keyPoints:
@Component: generic bean; all others are meta-annotations on it
@Repository: data access layer + exception translation (DataAccessException wrapping)
@Service: business layer — no extra behavior, purely semantic
@Controller: MVC layer — integrates with DispatcherServlet
@RestController = @Controller + @ResponseBody (returns JSON/XML directly)
All trigger @ComponentScan — no difference in bean creation

codeExample:
// Preferred: constructor injection
@Service
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class OrderService {
    private final OrderRepository repo;  // final, injected via constructor
    private final EmailService email;
}

keyPoints:
@Qualifier("beanName"): disambiguate when multiple beans of same type
@Primary: default bean when no qualifier specified
Combined: @Qualifier takes precedence over @Primary
Custom qualifiers: create @interface with @Qualifier meta-annotation
Profile-based: @Profile("dev") / @Profile("prod") for environment-specific beans
Naming convention: @Bean method name becomes bean name by default

@EnableAutoConfiguration: scans auto-config candidates from META-INF imports file
@ConditionalOnClass: only configure if class on classpath (e.g., DataSource if HikariCP present)
@ConditionalOnMissingBean: back off if user already defined the bean
@ConditionalOnProperty: enable based on config property
Debug: --debug flag prints auto-config report (what applied, what didn't, why)
Exclusion: @SpringBootApplication(exclude=DataSourceAutoConfiguration.class)

Activation: spring.profiles.active=dev (properties), --spring.profiles.active=prod (CLI)
application-dev.yml: loaded when dev profile active (overrides application.yml)
@Profile("prod"): bean/config only created for prod profile
@Profile({"dev","test"}): multiple profiles
Default profile: @Profile("default") — when no profile active
Cloud environments: inject profile via env vars SPRING_PROFILES_ACTIVE

codeExample:
@Bean
SecurityFilterChain filterChain(HttpSecurity http) throws Exception {
    return http
        .csrf(csrf -> csrf.disable())
        .addFilterBefore(jwtFilter, UsernamePasswordAuthenticationFilter.class)
        .authorizeHttpRequests(auth -> auth
            .requestMatchers("/api/auth/**").permitAll()
            .anyRequest().authenticated())
        .build();
}

@CircuitBreaker(name = "paymentService", fallbackMethod = "paymentFallback")
public PaymentResult processPayment(Order order) { ... }

public PaymentResult paymentFallback(Order order, Exception ex) {
    return PaymentResult.queued();
}
